into oblivion.

19:37.886 --> 19:41.180
Set us back a hundred years
with all these fucking stories.

19:41.180 --> 19:42.849
Look at this.
Give us a bad name.

19:42.849 --> 19:44.183
You know what they say?
They say,

19:44.183 --> 19:46.311
"Oh, there goes the Jew again."

19:46.311 --> 19:49.522
You don't care about
anyone but yourself.

19:49.522 --> 19:52.901
Who the fuck are you? And how
did you fucking get in here?

19:52.901 --> 19:54.694
You know, your grandfather
was just like you.

19:54.694 --> 19:56.821
My grandfather?

19:56.821 --> 19:58.531
Son of a bitch diva.

19:58.531 --> 20:00.575
Chevy Chase
of the Yiddish Theater.

20:00.575 --> 20:03.161
But for all his ass-fuckery,

20:03.161 --> 20:04.829
he was a great actor.

20:04.829 --> 20:07.206
W-Wait-wait, you...

20:07.206 --> 20:10.418
- you knew my grandfather?
- Not personally, no, but...

20:10.418 --> 20:12.712
But you know about him?

20:14.172 --> 20:17.133
Well, my-my-my father
rarely spoke about him.

20:17.133 --> 20:20.053
Well, your grandfather was

20:20.053 --> 20:21.596
imprisoned in the camps.

20:21.596 --> 20:24.057
And every Shabbos,

20:24.057 --> 20:25.767
late at night,

20:25.767 --> 20:28.895
your grandfather would perform.

20:28.895 --> 20:30.480
All the greats.

20:30.480 --> 20:33.691
Sholem Aleichem,
Brecht, Shakespeare.

20:33.691 --> 20:35.944
"Hath not a Jew eyes?

20:35.944 --> 20:38.071
Hath not a Jew hands, organs,

20:38.071 --> 20:40.740
dimensions, senses?

20:40.740 --> 20:42.992
If you prick us,

20:42.992 --> 20:44.827
do we not bleed?"

20:44.827 --> 20:47.747
The guards discovered him,
of course.

20:47.747 --> 20:49.916
They shot him twice. Dead.

20:49.916 --> 20:53.836
But every Shabbos

20:53.836 --> 20:57.256
he freed those men
in that cell block.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.927
Transporting them
to worlds far away.

21:03.262 --> 21:06.099
<i>Bullets on Mars 2?</i>

21:06.099 --> 21:10.019
The fuck is...
What the fuck is this?

21:11.479 --> 21:13.439
You once did <i>Hamlet.</i>

21:13.439 --> 21:15.108
You played in <i>Othello.</i>

21:15.108 --> 21:17.860
"Greatest young actor
of our time."

21:17.860 --> 21:19.278
What happened?

21:21.823 --> 21:23.825
I don't know.

21:25.159 --> 21:27.787
I don't know, it just, uh...

21:27.787 --> 21:29.622
it just happened.

21:31.332 --> 21:34.669
You are Fyvel Flazenstein's
grandchild.

21:36.671 --> 21:39.257
You're made
of the same stuff as he is.

21:39.257 --> 21:42.385
Believe me, I see him in you.

21:42.385 --> 21:45.263
And I see you, Leonard.

21:45.263 --> 21:47.306
I do, I see you.

21:49.100 --> 21:52.520
I'm here with an opportunity

21:52.520 --> 21:54.230
for you,

21:54.230 --> 21:56.858
greater than any role
you could ever play.

22:06.159 --> 22:07.785
Can I sit?

22:19.797 --> 22:21.758
You do what you want
with your life, Lonny,

22:21.758 --> 22:25.094
but if you want to do this,
you need to be sober.

22:25.094 --> 22:28.264
For our lives

22:28.264 --> 22:30.266
and for hers.

22:33.436 --> 22:35.688
I was in hell.

22:35.688 --> 22:38.524
Well, we don't believe in hell,
which is awesome, but

22:38.524 --> 22:41.235
I was in our version of hell.

22:41.235 --> 22:43.446
Last time I was using,

22:43.446 --> 22:45.448
every minute of every day,

22:45.448 --> 22:47.658
high off my tuchus.

22:47.658 --> 22:49.660
Snorting, sniffing,

22:49.660 --> 22:52.163
tasting, smacking,
downing, sucking

22:52.163 --> 22:55.333
everything and everyone,
so that I wouldn't

22:55.333 --> 22:58.377
see my face,

22:58.377 --> 23:01.964
so that I couldn't
remember my name,

23:01.964 --> 23:04.467
so I didn't know I was alone.

23:07.303 --> 23:08.596
So then, one day,

23:08.596 --> 23:11.057
this old man
comes to my trailer

23:11.057 --> 23:13.976
and he starts telling me
a story about my grandfather.

23:13.976 --> 23:15.895
About what a hero he was.

23:15.895 --> 23:17.814
And how I'm made of him.

23:17.814 --> 23:21.025
And how I could be
just like him.

23:23.486 --> 23:26.614
So I took the dagger

23:26.614 --> 23:28.491
and I joined a family.

23:32.120 --> 23:34.372
And I really felt that I...

23:36.624 --> 23:38.376
...was somebody, you know?

23:38.376 --> 23:41.838
That I... existed.

23:43.548 --> 23:45.550
And the funny thing is...

23:47.510 --> 23:49.804
...it was all a lie.

23:49.804 --> 23:52.974
He didn't know my grandfather.

23:52.974 --> 23:55.810
And I realize now,

23:55.810 --> 23:58.104
he didn't know me.

24:02.358 --> 24:04.610
I watched them all.

24:05.903 --> 24:07.530
Your films.

24:07.530 --> 24:10.449
And you are a terrible actor.

24:10.449 --> 24:12.285
Not the roles

24:12.285 --> 24:14.954
in your films.

24:14.954 --> 24:18.791
But this role, Lonny Flash.

24:18.791 --> 24:20.793
Because your greatest

24:20.793 --> 24:23.004
role is the one

24:23.004 --> 24:26.174
you've been born to play.

24:26.174 --> 24:30.303
Leonard Flazenstein.

24:30.303 --> 24:31.804
You.

24:31.804 --> 24:35.057
And I think she would agree.

24:35.057 --> 24:38.186
That is the role she would love.

24:38.186 --> 24:41.272
The one role Roxy
could love you as, too.

24:41.272 --> 24:43.191
The real you.

24:44.775 --> 24:47.153
God, you are really
good-looking.

24:48.696 --> 24:50.740
I-I really...
I find it annoying.

24:53.451 --> 24:55.870
We should go
find the Stammers.

24:55.870 --> 24:58.122
- Mm, Lonny.
- What?

24:58.122 --> 25:01.125
Chava sent the three of us
for a reason.

25:01.125 --> 25:02.668
You need me.

25:08.716 --> 25:09.842
<i>When we get there,</i>

25:09.842 --> 25:11.969
<i>I'll need you
to stay in the car.</i>

25:11.969 --> 25:13.471
<i>So, where
are we going, Harriet?</i>

25:13.471 --> 25:16.265
I know it's not simply
to round up some files.

25:18.601 --> 25:21.979
I'm going to find a man.

25:21.979 --> 25:25.399
A man I've been looking for
for a very long time.

25:25.399 --> 25:27.151
<i>O come ♪</i>

25:27.151 --> 25:30.154
<i>All ye faithful ♪</i>

25:30.154 --> 25:34.158
<i>Joyful and triumphant ♪</i>

25:34.158 --> 25:38.537
<i>O come ye, O come ye ♪</i>

25:38.537 --> 25:43.417
<i>To Bethlehem ♪</i>

25:43.417 --> 25:46.128
<i>Come and behold ♪</i>

25:46.128 --> 25:47.922
<i>Him ♪</i>

25:47.922 --> 25:51.133
<i>Born the King of Angels... ♪</i>

25:51.133 --> 25:53.970
Do they know any
Kool the Gang?

25:53.970 --> 25:57.056
<i>Adore him, O come... ♪</i>

25:57.056 --> 25:58.808
Meyer Offerman.

25:58.808 --> 26:00.935
<i>Adore him... ♪</i>

26:00.935 --> 26:04.313
Mother Superior gusted my wind

26:04.313 --> 26:05.773
in your direction.

26:05.773 --> 26:09.360
She said the orphanage
needed a new roof,

26:09.360 --> 26:11.779
new boiler, 20 new beds.

26:14.490 --> 26:17.326
And I happen to be in the market

26:17.326 --> 26:19.203
for making a sizable

26:19.203 --> 26:22.039
donation.

26:22.039 --> 26:23.666
Oh.

26:23.666 --> 26:26.377
That is quite charitable

26:26.377 --> 26:28.129
of you, Mr...

26:28.129 --> 26:31.215
- Offerman. Yeah.
- Offerman. Thank you.

26:31.215 --> 26:33.426
But if I may,

26:33.426 --> 26:35.303
what interest
does a bloke like you

26:35.303 --> 26:37.305
have in donating to the Church?

26:37.305 --> 26:39.724
A bloke like me?

26:39.724 --> 26:41.851
What, you mean a Jew?

26:41.851 --> 26:44.812
Well, what business
does a woman like you have

26:44.812 --> 26:47.773
donating herself
to the Church, hmm?

26:47.773 --> 26:49.900
I'm sorry?

26:49.900 --> 26:52.278
What? Your father was Jewish.

26:52.278 --> 26:55.156
Oh, Jesus was a Jew, yes.

26:55.156 --> 26:56.615
Not Jesus, Harriet.

26:57.491 --> 26:59.702
Your father, Rebecca.

26:59.702 --> 27:01.537
Your father.

27:01.537 --> 27:03.581
Hiram Kreutzer.

27:05.124 --> 27:08.169
You can still hear it,
can't you?

27:08.169 --> 27:11.172
The screams of the steam engine

27:11.172 --> 27:15.051
as-as your father
hands you off to a woman

27:15.051 --> 27:17.178
through the train window.

27:18.512 --> 27:21.057
Perhaps he told you you were
just going on a holiday.

27:21.057 --> 27:23.976
How long until you understood

27:23.976 --> 27:25.686
why your father did this?

27:30.649 --> 27:33.444
Now listen closely,
you wrinkled old prat.

27:33.444 --> 27:35.988
If you think I would
hesitate to cut your

27:35.988 --> 27:38.491
proliferous head
off your motherfucking neck

27:38.491 --> 27:41.494
in front of these
dear, dear, little angels,

27:41.494 --> 27:43.079
you are sorely mistaken.

27:43.079 --> 27:45.790
Thank you.

27:45.790 --> 27:48.459
This is precisely why I'm here.

27:48.459 --> 27:52.171
I read your file.
Oxford. MI6.

27:52.171 --> 27:55.966
My colleagues and I
are putting together a team

27:55.966 --> 28:00.304
to bring fugitive Nazi scum

28:00.304 --> 28:02.556
to their bloody end.

28:08.187 --> 28:10.189
Never.

28:10.189 --> 28:12.566
Sorry?

28:12.566 --> 28:14.652
You asked

28:14.652 --> 28:17.738
when I finally knew
what my father had done for me,

28:17.738 --> 28:20.616
and the answer is never because
I should have died with him.

28:20.616 --> 28:22.701
I would have sooner died
with him

28:22.701 --> 28:25.079
if it meant even
one more day in his arms.

28:25.079 --> 28:29.333
So, thank you, Mr. Offerman.
I'm sorry you came all this way.

28:30.668 --> 28:34.463
If you wish to repay your fare,

28:34.463 --> 28:36.715
to avenge your father's death,

28:36.715 --> 28:38.467
you're not gonna find that

28:38.467 --> 28:41.846
with pageants and charity.

28:41.846 --> 28:44.932
You must join this cause.

28:44.932 --> 28:47.143
It's the only way.

28:47.143 --> 28:51.689
Your father only
put you on that train

28:51.689 --> 28:55.776
so that one day

28:55.776 --> 28:58.612
you could get off.

29:03.909 --> 29:06.287
Don't be nervous.

29:06.287 --> 29:07.788
I'm not nervous. I'm Jewish.

29:07.788 --> 29:09.707
This is what we look like
all the time.

29:09.707 --> 29:11.208
Hello?

29:13.252 --> 29:16.505
- Hello?
- Shalom, shalom.

29:16.505 --> 29:20.468
My darling nephew. [gasps] Oh,

29:20.468 --> 29:23.262
my goodness, you must be...

29:23.262 --> 29:24.430
Clara.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.891
It's so lovely to meet you.

29:31.729 --> 29:34.231
Hmm, hmm.

29:34.231 --> 29:35.733
Look at you.

29:35.733 --> 29:37.985
I can hardly see
your <i>shyna punim</i>

29:37.985 --> 29:39.695
behind all those flowers.

29:39.695 --> 29:42.114
So thoughtful.

29:42.114 --> 29:44.450
Come in, come in.

30:16.774 --> 30:18.442
That's their hotel.

30:24.865 --> 30:28.702
This is delicious. Thank you.

30:28.702 --> 30:30.704
It's an old recipe.

30:30.704 --> 30:32.957
I'm sure you've
never had it before.

30:32.957 --> 30:34.833
It's a Jewish staple.

30:34.833 --> 30:38.212
Sam's great-great-grandmother's
recipe.

30:38.212 --> 30:41.924
One's history is everything.

30:41.924 --> 30:46.220
So, Chava, uh,
why South America?

30:46.220 --> 30:47.930
Hmm...

30:47.930 --> 30:51.225
Well, I-I-I lived in London
for a time.

30:51.225 --> 30:54.228
And I moved down here
about ten years ago for work.

30:54.228 --> 30:55.854
There was a particular account

30:55.854 --> 30:58.482
I was pursuing many years now.

30:58.482 --> 30:59.608
How wonderful.

30:59.608 --> 31:00.901
And did you land the account?

31:00.901 --> 31:03.779
Mm. Not yet,

31:03.779 --> 31:05.531
- but I love the chase.
- You know, Clara...

31:05.531 --> 31:07.992
...is studying

31:07.992 --> 31:10.703
neuropsychiatry at the Sorbonne.

31:10.703 --> 31:11.954
She's actually up for

31:11.954 --> 31:14.081
a big position
at a top research clinic.

31:14.081 --> 31:15.958
Wow.

31:15.958 --> 31:19.628
Neuropsychiatry.

31:19.628 --> 31:21.964
- What do your parents do, dear?
- Oh,

31:21.964 --> 31:24.592
they're art collectors in
London. They-they have a gallery

31:24.592 --> 31:26.885
down on Savile Row.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.512
Art collectors.

31:28.512 --> 31:31.515
Hmm. It's a nice

31:31.515 --> 31:33.183
pastime for rich people,

31:33.183 --> 31:35.185
isn't it?

31:35.185 --> 31:36.437
Collecting.

31:36.437 --> 31:38.105
Taking something that doesn't...

31:38.105 --> 31:40.190
doesn't quite belong to you

31:40.190 --> 31:42.234
but claiming it as your own.

31:44.737 --> 31:45.821
So...

31:45.821 --> 31:48.741
when is the big day?

31:48.741 --> 31:50.993
October 10th in Paris.

31:50.993 --> 31:52.119
October?

31:52.119 --> 31:55.706
I'll be losing you
so soon... Sam.

31:57.041 --> 31:59.877
But you'll be gaining me.

32:06.842 --> 32:08.844
So, it will be a Jewish wedding?

32:10.721 --> 32:13.390
You know, I still have
your great-grandfather's tallit.

32:13.390 --> 32:15.309
Not gonna be wearing a tallit.

32:15.309 --> 32:16.477
Why not?

32:16.477 --> 32:18.520
Because

32:18.520 --> 32:20.230
you marry a shiksa,

32:20.230 --> 32:22.399
you're going to erase
who you are?

32:22.399 --> 32:24.526
What your

32:24.526 --> 32:26.570
ancestors fought for?

32:26.570 --> 32:28.113
Died for?

32:29.907 --> 32:33.619
Your <i>safta</i> must be
rolling over in her grave.

32:34.912 --> 32:36.997
If Sam wants
a Jewish wedding,

32:36.997 --> 32:38.791
I would love to honor that.

32:40.250 --> 32:41.919
The past year and a half,

32:41.919 --> 32:43.545
I've learned
how to bake challah,

32:43.545 --> 32:45.964
I've sung Dayenu,
I-I've held two seders,

32:45.964 --> 32:48.384
I've spun dreidels,
I've listened

32:48.384 --> 32:50.552
to the shofar's blow
and the minyan chants

32:50.552 --> 32:52.805
and Lenny Bruce's
"I Am Not A Nut, Elect Me."

32:52.805 --> 32:54.932
I don't ever want

32:54.932 --> 32:56.600
Sam to erase who he is.

32:56.600 --> 32:58.310
I fell in love with him
for who he is,

32:58.310 --> 33:00.479
and that includes
his Jewishness.

33:00.479 --> 33:03.440
I don't know what

33:03.440 --> 33:04.983
you thought I'd be,

33:04.983 --> 33:07.820
but I love him, Chava,

33:07.820 --> 33:09.029
with all my heart.

33:09.029 --> 33:11.031
And...

33:11.031 --> 33:14.493
he loves me with all of his.

33:14.493 --> 33:18.580
He is the kindest,

33:18.580 --> 33:20.916
gentlest,

33:20.916 --> 33:22.459
most loyal person

33:22.459 --> 33:24.878
I know.

33:28.424 --> 33:30.718
I had a love once.

33:31.885 --> 33:35.472
One that I would make
a silly speech like that for.

33:37.808 --> 33:40.144
His name was Zev.

33:40.144 --> 33:42.563
We met after the war.

33:42.563 --> 33:45.482
We're both in the same line
of-of work.

33:45.482 --> 33:47.901
We fell in love.

33:49.528 --> 33:52.614
We were together for 20 years,
but then one of us

33:52.614 --> 33:54.825
put the other before the work.

33:54.825 --> 33:56.118
And the other...

33:56.118 --> 33:58.495
Well...

33:58.495 --> 34:00.831
she believes

34:00.831 --> 34:02.624
that the work

34:02.624 --> 34:04.918
is the most important
thing of all.

34:08.130 --> 34:11.258
Zev sounds
like a lucky man...

34:11.258 --> 34:14.428
to have been able to love you

34:14.428 --> 34:15.929
for as long as he did.

34:21.852 --> 34:23.645
Perhaps we should have
some more wine.

34:23.645 --> 34:25.189
I think we've, uh,
had enough wine, right?

34:25.189 --> 34:28.400
No, I'll... I'll join you,

34:28.400 --> 34:31.403
but could this shiksa

34:31.403 --> 34:33.197
use the loo first?

34:33.197 --> 34:36.450
Of course, dear.
It's just down that long hall.

34:45.584 --> 34:47.503
She's too good for you.

35:16.073 --> 35:18.492
Good morning,
I'm here to see...

35:18.492 --> 35:19.618
...my father.

35:51.775 --> 35:53.652
It's been a long time.

35:57.948 --> 36:00.242
Are you here for my confession?

36:03.120 --> 36:04.329
No.

36:06.123 --> 36:09.668
No, I'm here for mine.
Would that be all right?

36:09.668 --> 36:11.503
I...

36:47.873 --> 36:51.752
When I was a little girl,

36:51.752 --> 36:54.922
my father...

36:54.922 --> 36:56.924
he placed me on a train,

36:56.924 --> 37:01.261
a train that was supposed
to take me to a safe haven,

37:01.261 --> 37:05.515
and he promised me, my father,

37:05.515 --> 37:07.976
that one day
he would return for me

37:07.976 --> 37:10.729
and I would be back
in his arms again.

37:10.729 --> 37:14.024
And I'm here.

37:14.024 --> 37:18.111
I've traveled all this way,
traveled all this time,

37:18.111 --> 37:20.989
because my father lied.

37:24.034 --> 37:26.620
He promised me

37:26.620 --> 37:28.956
he would see me again one day,

37:28.956 --> 37:31.083
and I'm here

37:31.083 --> 37:33.251
to ask you why.

37:33.251 --> 37:36.004
I'm here to ask you why he lied.

37:36.004 --> 37:39.383
Because only you know.

37:39.383 --> 37:41.927
Only you can know.

37:41.927 --> 37:44.680
Only you have the answer

37:44.680 --> 37:47.516
because you are the answer.

37:47.516 --> 37:49.726
Because you turned

37:49.726 --> 37:51.895
that promise into a lie

37:51.895 --> 37:55.065
when you shot my father dead
at Bergen-Belsen,

37:55.065 --> 37:58.568
July 2, 1943.
Isn't that right,

37:58.568 --> 38:00.487
Herr Müntz?

38:12.749 --> 38:15.711
I am sorry to you.

38:34.771 --> 38:37.274
I'm sorry to you.

40:32.139 --> 40:32.973
Hi.

40:33.765 --> 40:34.808
How could I help you?

40:34.808 --> 40:37.018
<i>Hola.</i>

40:37.018 --> 40:38.520
My name
is Antonio Costa.

40:38.520 --> 40:42.065
These are my clients,
Kate and Hamish Hughes.

40:42.482 --> 40:45.902
They have just purchased
a vacation home nearby...

40:45.902 --> 40:47.154
...and are looking
to furnish it.

40:50.365 --> 40:52.659
I'm afraid we are
closing early today.

40:52.659 --> 40:56.079
We'll look around quickly.

40:56.079 --> 40:59.416
May I use your washroom?
It was quite a long trip.

41:00.834 --> 41:03.336
It's in back.

42:02.479 --> 42:05.148
Careful with that.

42:05.148 --> 42:06.274
Relax.

42:06.274 --> 42:07.776
Don't.

42:09.486 --> 42:10.612
What is this?

42:10.612 --> 42:12.197
- We don't know.
- It's not Hitler

42:12.197 --> 42:13.323
that they're harboring.

42:13.323 --> 42:16.201
It's Josef fucking Mengele.

42:16.201 --> 42:18.787
The Angel of Death.

42:18.787 --> 42:21.081
Where is he? Hmm?

42:21.081 --> 42:22.415
Where is Mengele?

42:22.415 --> 42:23.959
- He's not here.
- Gitta.

42:23.959 --> 42:26.044
Speak up. Where is he now?

42:26.044 --> 42:27.379
Dead.

42:27.379 --> 42:28.380
Bullshit.

42:28.380 --> 42:30.674
Three months ago,

42:30.674 --> 42:33.593
he went on vacation and...

42:33.593 --> 42:35.428
he got a stroke
while he was swimming

42:35.428 --> 42:36.638
and he drowned.

42:36.638 --> 42:40.100
We didn't know who he was
for a long time. Honest.

42:40.100 --> 42:43.937
It wasn't until a few years ago
that we discovered his identity.

42:43.937 --> 42:47.524
When he died,
we went to the papers.

42:47.524 --> 42:49.985
We tried to sell the story.

42:49.985 --> 42:54.030
Yeah, and then we got a call
from an old lady.

42:54.030 --> 42:57.117
She promised to get on a train
and bring us $2 million

42:57.117 --> 42:59.202
to keep quiet.

43:00.203 --> 43:02.414
The Crow.

43:02.414 --> 43:05.542
And with all that money...

43:05.542 --> 43:08.211
we'd never have to work again.

43:11.047 --> 43:12.424
It's the horseradish
that makes it.

43:12.424 --> 43:14.759
If anyone ever tells you
they don't like horseradish,

43:14.759 --> 43:16.344
you run in the other direction.

43:16.344 --> 43:18.722
What are the cages for?

43:24.227 --> 43:26.354
I'm a part-time
illusionist, dear.

43:26.354 --> 43:28.023
Didn't Sam tell you?

43:28.023 --> 43:29.524
Aunt Chava's an artist.

43:29.524 --> 43:31.151
A performance artist.

43:31.151 --> 43:33.528
There are surveillance photos

43:33.528 --> 43:37.324
and maps and names
of SS officers

43:37.324 --> 43:39.576
and knives and guns.

43:39.576 --> 43:41.953
Yes.

43:41.953 --> 43:43.455
We hunt Nazis.

43:47.542 --> 43:49.461
She's joking.

43:49.461 --> 43:52.130
- She's-she's joking.
- I'm not joking.

43:52.130 --> 43:55.592
That is precisely what we do.

43:55.592 --> 43:57.218
We hunt Nazis

43:57.218 --> 44:00.638
and we rid them from this Earth.

44:00.638 --> 44:02.432
If Clara is to be family,

44:02.432 --> 44:05.477
she has a right to know what
the family business is, Jonah.

44:09.773 --> 44:13.151
His name is Jonah,
as in "and the whale."

44:13.151 --> 44:14.778
Jonah Heidelbaum.

44:14.778 --> 44:17.447
Not sure where
Sam Rabinow came from,

44:17.447 --> 44:19.199
- but it has a certain ring.
- Clara.

44:19.199 --> 44:21.159
Clara, don't...

44:21.159 --> 44:23.078
Clara!

44:23.078 --> 44:25.497
It's better this way.

44:43.223 --> 44:46.017
Hey. I got something.

45:06.287 --> 45:08.706
Ah, nothing but dreck.

45:13.002 --> 45:15.213
Murrayleh...

45:17.048 --> 45:20.176
They think I am incapable.

45:20.176 --> 45:21.678
Old.

45:24.097 --> 45:27.600
You know how I know I'm not old?

45:29.853 --> 45:32.397
Because I was
supposed to grow old

45:32.397 --> 45:34.315
with you.

45:42.490 --> 45:44.117
Hello?

45:50.165 --> 45:52.417
<i>Momentito, momentito.</i>

46:07.682 --> 46:08.975
Hola.

46:08.975 --> 46:11.394
Oh, gracias.

46:11.394 --> 46:13.480
Come on, come on.

46:46.179 --> 46:48.264
For fuck's sake.

46:52.644 --> 46:54.312
Fuck off.

46:56.981 --> 46:58.483
Jesus Christ.

46:58.483 --> 47:00.568
Let me explain.

47:00.568 --> 47:02.612
- Just give me a minute,
I'll explain everything.
- No. No, why?

47:02.612 --> 47:05.615
Why-why should I listen
to you, Jonah?

47:05.615 --> 47:07.867
Everything you've
ever said is a lie.

47:07.867 --> 47:08.868
You want to know the truth?

47:08.868 --> 47:10.954
Yeah.

47:10.954 --> 47:13.748
Three years ago, I woke up
in the middle of the night

47:13.748 --> 47:15.375
to see a man murder
my grandmother.

47:15.375 --> 47:18.419
She bled out in my arms. I found
out later that she died because

47:18.419 --> 47:21.256
she spent the last year
hunting Nazi war criminals.

47:21.256 --> 47:24.217
This five-foot-nothing,
little old lady was killed

47:24.217 --> 47:26.511
by the very Nazi
she was hunting, so I...

47:26.511 --> 47:28.888
took her place after she died.

47:28.888 --> 47:31.432
I found the man who killed her
and then I found dozens more.

47:31.432 --> 47:33.268
Why the late nights,

47:33.268 --> 47:34.769
why the screams in my sleep,

47:34.769 --> 47:36.688
the-the name change,
it's because of this.

47:36.688 --> 47:39.399
It's because it never ends, and
I'm out here trying to end it,

47:39.399 --> 47:41.943
once and for all,
so I can have a life with you,

47:41.943 --> 47:43.403
- with the woman that I love.
- No.

47:44.404 --> 47:46.322
- Down! Down!
- What the fuck?

47:46.322 --> 47:48.324
- Jonah.
- Listen, when I say
go to the bathroom, all right,

47:48.324 --> 47:49.659
- you're gonna go. Go, go, go!
- What the fuck?

47:49.659 --> 47:51.035
- Jonah!
- Hide and don't come out.

47:52.287 --> 47:54.372
Jonah.

47:57.041 --> 47:58.293
Come on out, Jonah.

48:02.630 --> 48:04.924
Jonah.

48:06.593 --> 48:08.219
Jonah.

48:10.972 --> 48:12.557
Hey, Jonah.

48:15.560 --> 48:16.603
Jonah.

48:23.526 --> 48:25.320
Jonah!

48:26.738 --> 48:28.197
Jonah.

48:30.491 --> 48:32.035
Jonah!

48:44.839 --> 48:46.090
Come and get me!

48:48.092 --> 48:50.845
Move! Move! Get out of the way.

49:37.600 --> 49:39.310
Move!

50:28.568 --> 50:31.612
Look, I'm sorry about before.

50:34.699 --> 50:39.454
I think the... I think
the problem might be that I'm...

50:39.454 --> 50:42.290
You know, I'm still
in love with you.

50:42.290 --> 50:45.418
Wait until you're sober.

50:45.418 --> 50:48.171
Look, I can clean my shit up.
You know I can do that.

50:48.171 --> 50:50.715
- We are just not a good fit.
- How can you say that?

50:50.715 --> 50:52.425
Because I can't take care
of you anymore.

50:52.425 --> 50:54.385
It is a full-time job,

50:54.385 --> 50:57.430
and I have a child
already, Lonny.

50:57.430 --> 50:59.182
And I don't have
any more to give.

51:19.577 --> 51:21.746
Joe.

51:23.956 --> 51:27.251
Joe. Joe.

51:33.800 --> 51:35.968
Joe. Joe.

51:46.854 --> 51:49.023
<i>Policía. Policía.</i>

52:08.334 --> 52:10.002
No! Let me go!

52:10.002 --> 52:12.421
- Let me go!
- Clara!

52:19.720 --> 52:22.515
Clara!

52:24.350 --> 52:25.852
Clara!

52:27.144 --> 52:28.437
Clara!

52:31.232 --> 52:33.317
Clara!

52:33.317 --> 52:35.695
Sam!
